brief_description of the content in the: The source URL provides information about a JetBrains inspection rule that reports standard setter methods in Java that can be replaced by the Lombok @Setter annotation. The rule only applies when the Lombok library is configured in the project. The page also provides a link to the Lombok site for instructions on how to 'unlombok' or remove the Lombok annotations.
generated_rule_explanation from GPT-4: The rule 'lombok-setter-may-be-used' checks all classes in the project. For each class, it checks all methods. If a method's name starts with 'set' and the method has a parameter of type 'Object', it asserts that the method has the 'lombok.Setter' annotation. If the method does not have this annotation, it generates a message indicating that the standard setter method can be replaced by the Lombok @Setter annotation.
